<TITLE> Ijtema ends with 2 million joining Akheri Munajat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 1 (bdnews24.com)The 45th Bishwa Ijtema, the second largest annual congregation of Muslims worldwide after the Hajj, drew to a close Sunday afternoon with 2 million devotees from home and abroad offering Akheri Munajat (closing prayers) in unseasonably fine weather. Maulana Zobayrul Hasan from India led the Akheri Munajat that continued for 15 minutes from 1:15 pm to 1:30 pm. Maulana Saad delivered the Akheri Boyan (closing statement) prior to the prayers. The size of the closing congregation was estimated at nearly two million, said the organisers. President Iajuddin Ahmed, prime minister Sheikh Hasina and BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia and other VIPsattended the closing prayers. A record figure of 10,500 foreigners joined the Ijtema this year, enjoying unusually warm weather. Last year's congress was cut short after just one day due to inclement weather. bdnew
